# Update README.md in the main branch:
1. Open your terminal.
2. Navigate to the directory of your local Git repository.
3. Pull the latest changes from the main branch (assuming you're currently on the main branch):
   ```git pull origin main```
4. Edit the README.md file with the changes you want to make.
5. Save the changes.
6. Add the changes to Git:
   ```git add README.md```
7. Commit the changes with an appropriate commit message:
   ```git commit -m 'Update README.md'```
8. Push the changes to the main branch on GitHub:
   ```git push origin main```
